Conflict of interest statement: Conflict of Interest: No conflict of interest wasdeclared by the authors.19. Turk J Surg. 2018 Mar 1;34(1):57-59. doi: 10.5152/UCD.2016.3654. eCollection2018.First experience with a new technique: Portable gamma camera usage for sentinellymph node identification in a patient with breast cancer.Koç ZP(1), Kara PPÖ(1), Berkeşoğlu M(2), Akça T(2).Author information: (1)Department of Nuclear Medicine, Mersin University School of Medicine, Mersin, Turkey.(2)Department of General Surgery, Mersin University School of Medicine, Mersin,Turkey.The newest development in sentinel lymph node imaging is portable gamma probeimaging. In this case report, results of all SLN detection methods were analyzed.The patient was imaged using a large field-of-view gamma camera with additionalblue dye administration and intraoperative localization of sentinel lymph nodeusing both gamma probe and portable gamma camera was performed. In this casereport, the value of additional portable gamma camera imaging was analyzed.DOI: 10.5152/UCD.2016.3654 PMCID: PMC5937662PMID: 29756109 